UNITED STATES v. BERNSTEIN. No. 12143. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. March 5, 1948. Rehearing Denied April 20, 1948. Lansing L. Mitchell and John N. McKay, Asst. U. S. Attys., both of New Orleans, La., for appellant. James David McNeill and Warren M. Simon, both of New Orleans, La., for ap-pellee.

Before HUTCHESON, HOLMES, and McCORD, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

A careful examination of the record convinces us that the order appealed from, dismissing the case without prejudice, after a delay in its prosecution of more than sixteen months, was not reversible error; The judgment is affirmed.
